x4freetext: - similar exp., additional info (see ERR-ANALYS).
Uncertainty of absolute
calibration of used spectrometer.
Irradiation time was 11 minutes.
The measurements were began after 15 minutes
of end of irradiation, approximately. 34 measurements
have been executed during to 18 hours. Each measurement
was from 10 to 60 minutes. Additional measurement has
been executed after 1 day, 25 days and half year.
The stack has contained aluminum and lead
foils. All foils have diameter 30 mm. Thickness was
0.1 mm of lead. All targets in this stack were
surrounded by additional identical foils to exclude
activity loss.
-By Compiler- Any information about energy
degradation in used stack is absent.
Table on p.153 from 97OBNIN,153,1997.
Last checking has been done.
SD: Corrections in all Subents. ASSUMED
deleted (info given in MONITOR reaction). ERR-ANALYS
updated. ASSUM1/2 -> MONIT1/2.

x4freetext: * by Compiler * According to ENSDF ground state of
198-Bi has half-life 10.3 minutes. 198-Bi has two
isomers. First one has half-life 11.6 minutes, second
one has half-life 7.7 seconds. Second isomer state
decays to first isomer. First isomer does not decay to
ground state of 198-Bi. Therfore authors`
interpretation maybe doubtful.
Uncertainty includes statistical error and
uncertainty of absolute calibration of gamma
spectrometer.

were not be included in this error.
